<section class="kk-section kk-section-light">
    <div class="kk-section-header">
        <h2>Gear Guide</h2>
        <p>Practical, budget-friendly gear suggestions to pair with your Catch Keeper data.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h3>Core rod &amp; reel setups</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>All-purpose casting combo</strong> – Medium-heavy, fast-action rod with a 7:1 reel for jigs, Texas rigs, and spinnerbaits.</li>
                <li><strong>Finesse spinning combo</strong> – Medium-light or medium spinning rod with 2500-size reel for drop-shots, Ned rigs, and small swimbaits.</li>
                <li><strong>Power setup</strong> – Heavy rod with strong line for frogging, punching grass, or big swimbaits (where allowed).</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h3>Terminal tackle &amp; must-haves</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Assortment of offset worm hooks and EWG hooks</li>
                <li>Fluorocarbon and braid main lines plus a few leaders</li>
                <li>Tungsten or lead weights from 1/8 oz to 1/2 oz</li>
                <li>Snap swivels and split-ring pliers for quick lure changes</li>
                <li>Sharp scissors or line cutters and a small toolkit</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row" style="margin-top: 20px;">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h3>Confidence bait lineup</h3>
            <p>
                Catch Keeper becomes most powerful when you repeatedly log a consistent bait lineup. Consider keeping:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>Compact jig with matching trailer</li>
                <li>Stick bait or finesse worm for slow presentations</li>
                <li>Squarebill crankbait for shallow cover</li>
                <li>Swimbait or chatterbait for covering water</li>
                <li>Topwater walking bait or frog for low-light windows</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h3>Tech on the boat or bank</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Scale &amp; measuring board</strong> – Accurately log weights and lengths.</li>
                <li><strong>Phone with Catch Keeper</strong> – Your portable logbook and camera.</li>
                <li><strong>Portable charger</strong> – Keeps your device alive on long days.</li>
                <li><strong>Weather-friendly storage</strong> – Dry bag or waterproof case for electronics.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>
